	<body class="">
		


<meta charset="UTF-8">
<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Lato:wght@300;400;700&display=swap');
  * { margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing:border-box; }
  body { font-family:'Lato',sans-serif; background:#f5f0eb; color:#2d1b3d; }

<p>  .page {
    width: 794px;
    min-height: 1123px;
    background: #f5f0eb;
    margin: 0 auto 40px;
    padding: 70px 80px;
    position: relative;
    page-break-after: always;
  }</p>
<p>  /* INTRO PAGE */
  .intro-accent {
    width: 60px; height: 4px;
    background: #7c4d8a;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }
  .intro-eyebrow {
    font-family:&#39;Lato&#39;,sans-serif;
    font-size:11px; font-weight:700;
    letter-spacing:3px; text-transform:uppercase;
    color:#7c4d8a; margin-bottom:16px;
  }
  .intro-heading {
    font-family:&#39;Playfair Display&#39;,serif;
    font-size:34px; line-height:1.3;
    color:#2d1b3d; margin-bottom:24px;
  }
  .intro-body {
    font-size:16px; line-height:1.8;
    color:#3d2a4a; margin-bottom:16px;
  }
  .intro-callout {
    border-left:3px solid #7c4d8a;
    padding:16px 20px;
    background:#ede6f5;
    border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;
    font-size:15px; line-height:1.7;
    color:#2d1b3d; margin:24px 0;
    font-style:italic;
  }</p>
<p>  /* HOW TO USE */
  .how-box {
    background:#fff;
    border-radius:12px;
    padding:32px 36px;
    margin-top:32px;
    border:1px solid #ddd4e8;
  }
  .how-box h2 {
    font-family:&#39;Playfair Display&#39;,serif;
    font-size:22px; color:#2d1b3d;
    margin-bottom:16px;
  }
  .how-box p {
    font-size:15px; line-height:1.8;
    color:#4a3558;
  }</p>
<p>  /* QUESTION PAGES */
  .q-header {
    display:flex; align-items:center;
    gap:16px; margin-bottom:40px;
  }
  .q-number {
    width:48px; height:48px;
    background:#7c4d8a; border-radius:50%;
    display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;
    font-family:&#39;Playfair Display&#39;,serif;
    font-size:22px; color:#fff; font-weight:700;
    flex-shrink:0;
  }
  .q-title {
    font-family:&#39;Playfair Display&#39;,serif;
    font-size:26px; line-height:1.3;
    color:#2d1b3d;
  }
  .q-divider {
    height:1px; background:#ddd4e8;
    margin-bottom:32px;
  }
  .answer-option {
    display:flex; align-items:flex-start;
    gap:16px; padding:18px 20px;
    border-radius:10px; margin-bottom:12px;
    border:1.5px solid #ddd4e8;
    background:#fff;
  }
  .answer-option.opt-a { border-color:#c8b8d8; background:#f9f5ff; }
  .answer-circle {
    width:24px; height:24px; border-radius:50%;
    border:2px solid #b09ec0;
    flex-shrink:0; margin-top:2px;
  }
  .answer-text {
    font-size:16px; line-height:1.5; color:#2d1b3d;
  }
  .q-insight {
    margin-top:28px;
    padding:16px 20px;
    background:#ede6f5;
    border-radius:8px;
    border-left:3px solid #7c4d8a;
    font-size:14px; line-height:1.7;
    color:#4a3558; font-style:italic;
  }</p>
<p>  /* QUESTIONS 2-PER-PAGE layout */
  .q-block {
    margin-bottom:40px;
    padding-bottom:36px;
    border-bottom:1px solid #ddd4e8;
  }
  .q-block:last-child { border-bottom:none; }
  .q-block .q-num-inline {
    display:inline-flex; width:36px; height:36px;
    background:#7c4d8a; border-radius:50%;
    align-items:center; justify-content:center;
    font-family:&#39;Playfair Display&#39;,serif;
    font-size:16px; color:#fff; font-weight:700;
    margin-right:12px; vertical-align:middle;
    flex-shrink:0;
  }
  .q-block .q-question {
    font-family:&#39;Playfair Display&#39;,serif;
    font-size:20px; line-height:1.4; color:#2d1b3d;
    margin-bottom:20px; display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:12px;
  }
  .q-block .answer-option {
    padding:14px 18px; margin-bottom:8px;
  }
  .q-block .answer-text { font-size:15px; }
  .q-block .q-insight { margin-top:16px; font-size:13px; }</p>
<p>  /* RESULTS PAGE */
  .results-heading {
    font-family:&#39;Playfair Display&#39;,serif;
    font-size:36px; color:#2d1b3d;
    margin-bottom:8px;
  }
  .results-sub {
    font-size:15px; color:#7c4d8a; margin-bottom:36px;
    font-weight:700; letter-spacing:1px; text-transform:uppercase;
  }
  .result-card {
    background:#fff; border-radius:12px;
    padding:28px 32px; margin-bottom:20px;
    border:1.5px solid #ddd4e8;
  }
  .result-card.card-green { border-color:#a8c5a0; background:#f4faf3; }
  .result-card.card-yellow { border-color:#d4b896; background:#fdf8f2; }
  .result-card.card-red { border-color:#c4a0b8; background:#fdf4f9; }
  .result-label {
    font-family:&#39;Lato&#39;,sans-serif; font-size:11px;
    font-weight:700; letter-spacing:2px;
    text-transform:uppercase; margin-bottom:10px;
  }
  .result-label.green { color:#4a8a42; }
  .result-label.yellow { color:#a07030; }
  .result-label.red { color:#7c4d8a; }
  .result-text {
    font-size:16px; line-height:1.7; color:#2d1b3d;
  }
  .result-note {
    margin-top:28px; padding:20px 24px;
    background:#2d1b3d; border-radius:10px;
    color:#f5f0eb; font-size:15px; line-height:1.7;
    font-style:italic;
  }</p>
<p>  /* CTA PAGE */
  .cta-page { text-align:center; }
  .cta-eyebrow {
    font-size:11px; font-weight:700;
    letter-spacing:3px; text-transform:uppercase;
    color:#7c4d8a; margin-bottom:20px;
  }
  .cta-heading {
    font-family:&#39;Playfair Display&#39;,serif;
    font-size:36px; line-height:1.3;
    color:#2d1b3d; margin-bottom:20px;
  }
  .cta-body {
    font-size:16px; line-height:1.8;
    color:#3d2a4a; max-width:580px;
    margin:0 auto 32px;
  }
  .cta-features {
    text-align:left; max-width:500px;
    margin:0 auto 40px;
  }
  .cta-feature {
    display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:flex-start;
    margin-bottom:14px; font-size:15px;
    color:#2d1b3d; line-height:1.6;
  }
  .cta-bullet {
    width:20px; height:20px; background:#7c4d8a;
    border-radius:50%; flex-shrink:0; margin-top:2px;
    display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;
    color:#fff; font-size:11px; font-weight:700;
  }
  .cta-btn {
    display:inline-block;
    background:#2d1b3d; color:#f5f0eb;
    font-family:&#39;Lato&#39;,sans-serif; font-size:17px;
    font-weight:700; padding:20px 48px;
    border-radius:8px; text-decoration:none;
    letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:12px;
  }
  .cta-price {
    font-size:14px; color:#7c4d8a;
    font-weight:700; margin-bottom:32px;
  }
  .cta-footer {
    font-size:13px; color:#9a8aaa;
    font-style:italic; margin-top:48px;
  }</p>
<p>  /* PAGE FOOTER */
  .page-footer {
    position:absolute; bottom:32px; left:80px; right:80px;
    display:flex; justify-content:space-between;
    align-items:center;
    border-top:1px solid #ddd4e8; padding-top:12px;
  }
  .page-footer-brand {
    font-size:11px; color:#9a8aaa;
    letter-spacing:1px; text-transform:uppercase;
  }
  .page-footer-num {
    font-size:11px; color:#9a8aaa;
  }</p>
<p>  @media print {
    .page { margin:0; }
  }
</style><p></p>



<!-- PAGE 0: COVER -->
<div class="page" style="padding:0; overflow:hidden; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; background:#f5f0eb;">
  <img src="data:image/png;base64," style="width:100%; height:100%; object-fit:cover; display:block;">
</div>

<!-- PAGE 1: BEFORE YOU START -->
<div class="page">
  <div class="intro-eyebrow">A 5-Minute Clarity Check</div>
  <div class="intro-accent"></div>
  <h1 class="intro-heading">Before You Start</h1>

  <p class="intro-body">Something felt off. That's why you're here.</p>
  <p class="intro-body">Not a fight. Not a blowup. Just a low hum of <em>something's not right</em> that you can't quite explain.</p>
  <p class="intro-body">You've been replaying the conversation. Giving him the benefit of the doubt. Wondering if you're being too sensitive, too suspicious, too much.</p>

  <div class="intro-callout">You're not.</div>

  <p class="intro-body">This isn't a checklist to prove he's a bad person. It's a way to stop arguing with yourself long enough to see what's actually there.</p>

  <div class="how-box">
    <h2>How to Use This</h2>
    <p>Read each question. Answer based on <strong>what he does</strong> — not what he says, not what he meant, not what you hope is true.</p>
    <br>
    <p>Don't soften your answers to be fair. You're not on trial here. You're just looking.</p>
    <br>
    <p><strong>Add up your answers.</strong> Note which column you chose most — first, second, or third option. Your results are on the last page.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="page-footer">
    <span class="page-footer-brand">Red Flag or Overthinking? · @thedateprofiler</span>
    <span class="page-footer-num">1</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- PAGE 2: QUESTIONS 1 & 2 -->
<div class="page">

  <div class="q-block">
    <div class="q-question">
      <span class="q-num-inline">1</span>
      <span>Do his words and his actions match — without you having to explain it to yourself?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option opt-a">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">Yes — what he says lines up with what he does</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">Sometimes, but I usually fill in the gaps for him</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">No — I do a lot of interpreting</span>
    </div>
    <div class="q-insight">Healthy interest doesn't need translation.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-block">
    <div class="q-question">
      <span class="q-num-inline">2</span>
      <span>When you bring up something that bothered you, what happens?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option opt-a">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">He listens and asks questions</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">He brushes it off or makes it a joke</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">It somehow becomes about him</span>
    </div>
    <div class="q-insight">Watch for explanations that reroute responsibility instead of addressing what you said.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-footer">
    <span class="page-footer-brand">Red Flag or Overthinking? · @thedateprofiler</span>
    <span class="page-footer-num">2</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- PAGE 3: QUESTIONS 3 & 4 -->
<div class="page">

  <div class="q-block">
    <div class="q-question">
      <span class="q-num-inline">3</span>
      <span>After spending time with him — or just talking to him — how do you feel?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option opt-a">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">Settled</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">Unsure — I'm replaying things</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">Tense, self-critical, a little on edge</span>
    </div>
    <div class="q-insight">Your body keeps score before your brain catches up.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-block">
    <div class="q-question">
      <span class="q-num-inline">4</span>
      <span>Has trust built on its own, or has he asked for it?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option opt-a">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">It's grown naturally over time</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">He talks about trust a lot</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">I feel pressured to just trust him</span>
    </div>
    <div class="q-insight">Trust isn't something you give on request. It accumulates. Or it doesn't.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-footer">
    <span class="page-footer-brand">Red Flag or Overthinking? · @thedateprofiler</span>
    <span class="page-footer-num">3</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- PAGE 4: QUESTIONS 5, 6 & 7 -->
<div class="page">

  <div class="q-block">
    <div class="q-question">
      <span class="q-num-inline">5</span>
      <span>When something doesn't add up, do you feel okay slowing down — or do you feel like you can't?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option opt-a">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">I feel allowed to pause</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">I worry about losing him if I do</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">Slowing down feels like a risk</span>
    </div>
    <div class="q-insight">Urgency is a tactic. Connection doesn't require speed.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-block">
    <div class="q-question">
      <span class="q-num-inline">6</span>
      <span>Are you figuring out if he's right for you — or are you working to make sure he stays interested?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option opt-a">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">I'm assessing fit</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">I try not to rock the boat</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">I'm managing his reactions</span>
    </div>
    <div class="q-insight">If you're performing, you're not choosing.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-block">
    <div class="q-question">
      <span class="q-num-inline">7</span>
      <span>If nothing changed from this point forward, would you be okay with that?</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option opt-a">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">Yes — relieved, actually</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">Neutral</span>
    </div>
    <div class="answer-option">
      <div class="answer-circle"></div>
      <span class="answer-text">No — disappointed, still hoping</span>
    </div>
    <div class="q-insight">Hope isn't data.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-footer">
    <span class="page-footer-brand">Red Flag or Overthinking? · @thedateprofiler</span>
    <span class="page-footer-num">4</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- PAGE 5: RESULTS -->
<div class="page">
  <div class="results-heading">Your Results</div>
  <div class="results-sub">Add up which column you chose most</div>

  <div class="result-card card-green">
    <div class="result-label green">Mostly First Options</div>
    <p class="result-text">Trust is forming at a reasonable pace. Stay observant without becoming vigilant. What you're seeing is data — keep collecting it.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="result-card card-yellow">
    <div class="result-label yellow">A Mix of First and Second</div>
    <p class="result-text">Slow down. Don't add emotional investment yet. You need more time and more information before you decide what this is.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="result-card card-red">
    <div class="result-label red">Several Third Options</div>
    <p class="result-text">This isn't overthinking. This is your pattern recognition working exactly the way it should. Something is asking for your attention.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="result-note">
    Nothing here says run. But something says pause — and that's worth listening to.<br><br>
    Confusion isn't a flaw. It's usually a sign that clarity is being withheld. You don't need to get cold. You don't need to get cynical. You just need to learn to read what's actually in front of you before emotion gets too far ahead of evidence.
  </div>

  <div class="page-footer">
    <span class="page-footer-brand">Red Flag or Overthinking? · @thedateprofiler</span>
    <span class="page-footer-num">5</span>
  </div>
</div>

